Reasoning: The paper focuses on a vision-based system for lane detection and classification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) categories. The use of Kalman filter and particle filter for lane modeling and tracking suggests the involvement of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The paper also discusses the validation of the proposed system and dataset, which may fall under the category of evaluation and testing (cs.LG) and cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CR).
